This is a missed-optimization in InstCombine.

The following program reveals the missed optimization.
The source program is
```llvm
define i1 @test_icmp_sgt_and_negpow2_c(i32 %add) {
  %and = and i32 %add, -32
  %cmp = icmp sgt i32 %and, 16
  ret i1 %cmp
}

```

However, current LLVM cannot optimize the source program. The expected optimized program is
```llvm
define i1 @test_icmp_sgt_and_negpow2_c(i32 %add) {
  %cmp = icmp sgt i32 %add, 31
  ret i1 %cmp
}

```
Please modify the following code in llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp:InstCombinerImpl::foldICmpAndConstConst to implement the missed optimization:
